1. An application running on EC2 needs basic networking, multiple IPs, and security groups. No high-bandwidth requirement. Which option should be used?

A. ENI
B. ENA
C. EFA
D. VPN Interface

‚úî Correct Answer: A. ENI
Explanation: ENI is the basic virtual NIC for standard workloads.

2. A solution architect needs high throughput and low latency networking for inter-instance communication. Which NIC is MOST suitable?

A. ENI
B. ENA
C. EFA
D. NAT instance

‚úî Correct Answer: B. ENA
Explanation: ENA supports high-performance networking up to 100 Gbps.

3. A machine learning workload requires extremely low-latency communication and OS bypass. Which AWS NIC should you choose?

A. Secondary ENI
B. ENA
C. EFA
D. ClassicLink

‚úî Correct Answer: C. EFA
Explanation: Only EFA provides OS-bypass and HPC-level low latency.

4. Which feature is supported ONLY by EFA and not by ENI or ENA?

A. Security groups
B. OS bypass
C. Multiple private IPs
D. IPv6 addresses

‚úî Correct Answer: B. OS bypass
Explanation: OS bypass is unique to EFA for HPC workloads.

5. In OS bypass mode, EFA traffic is restricted to:

A. Multiple VPCs
B. Multiple subnets
C. Same subnet only
D. Across Availability Zones

‚úî Correct Answer: C. Same subnet only
Explanation: EFA in OS bypass mode cannot route traffic outside a single subnet.

6. Which network interface is available on all EC2 instance types?

A. ENI
B. ENA
C. EFA
D. Intel VF Adapter

‚úî Correct Answer: A. ENI
Explanation: ENI is supported on every instance type; ENA/EFA have restrictions.

7. A workload requires up to 100 Gbps network speed. Which NIC supports this?

A. ENI
B. ENA
C. EFA only
D. None

‚úî Correct Answer: B. ENA
Explanation: ENA supports up to 100 Gbps networking.

8. A parallel scientific simulation using MPI needs the lowest latency possible. Best NIC?

A. ENI
B. ENA
C. EFA
D. Secondary Private IP

‚úî Correct Answer: C. EFA
Explanation: MPI-based workloads are tightly coupled ‚Üí EFA is designed for this.

9. What happens when using EFA in non‚ÄìOS-bypass mode?

A. Traffic cannot be routed
B. Traffic can be routed across subnets
C. EFA is disabled
D. Only IPv6 works

‚úî Correct Answer: B. Traffic can be routed across subnets
Explanation: Routing limits apply ONLY in OS-bypass mode.

10. You need a NIC supporting SR-IOV for high I/O performance and low CPU usage. Which one?

A. ENI
B. ENA
C. EFA
D. Internet Gateway

‚úî Correct Answer: B. ENA
Explanation: ENA uses SR-IOV for enhanced performance.


1Ô∏è‚É£ ENI ‚Äì Elastic Network Interface (Basic NIC)

Use case: General-purpose networking (web servers, app servers, DB servers).
Supported on: ALL EC2 instance types.

Key Features (MUST remember):

Primary private IPv4 address

Multiple secondary IPv4 addresses

1 Elastic IP per private IPv4

IPv6 support

One or more security groups

MAC address

Attach/detach between instances in the same AZ

When to choose ENI (Exam Clue):

No high-performance requirements

Basic VPC networking

Regular workloads

2Ô∏è‚É£ ENA ‚Äì Elastic Network Adapter (High Performance NIC)

Use case: High throughput + low latency networking.
Supported on: Selected EC2 instance families (HVM only).

Key Features:

Uses SR-IOV (Single Root I/O Virtualization)

High performance:

Up to 100 Gbps network speed

Higher PPS (Packets per second)

Lower CPU utilization

Exam Clue (VERY IMPORTANT):

If the question asks:
‚úî "High bandwidth?"
‚úî "Low instance-to-instance latency?"
‚úî "Need high PPS?"
üëâ Choose ENA over ENI.

3Ô∏è‚É£ EFA ‚Äì Elastic Fabric Adapter (Specialized HPC NIC)

Use case:

HPC (High Performance Computing)

Machine Learning

Tightly coupled cluster workloads (parallel computing)

Key Features:

Builds on ENA, but adds:
‚úî OS-bypass feature
‚úî Direct communication between application & NIC hardware
‚úî Ultra-low latency

Comparable performance to on-prem HPC clusters

Two Modes of Operation:
A) OS bypass mode (Very important exam point):

SUPER low latency

Traffic cannot be routed

Must stay within a single subnet

For tightly-coupled HPC tasks
(MPI-based workloads like CFD, weather modeling, seismic processing, ML training)

B) Non‚ÄìOS bypass mode:

Works like ENA

Traffic IS routable across subnets

Exam Clue:

If the question involves:
‚úî MPI workloads
‚úî HPC cluster
‚úî ML training with ultra-fast communication
‚úî Need direct NIC access
üëâ Choose EFA.

üî• Differences Summary Table (Exam Speed Revision)
Feature	                            ENI	                       ENA	                                    EFA
Performance	                     Basic	                       High	                                 Ultra-high
Use case        	          General workloads        High network throughput, low latency	          HPC, ML, tightly coupled apps
OS bypass                     	‚ùå No	                   ‚ùå No                                        	‚úî Yes
Subnet routing               	‚úî Yes                   	‚úî Yes	                                      ‚ùå No (OS bypass mode)
Instance support               	All types	          Limited                                           	Limited
Max speed	Low/Standard	Up to 100 Gbps	Highest available
üìå Most Important Exam Triggers
‚úî "High-performance networking" ‚Üí ENA
‚úî "HPC / MPI / tightly coupled apps" ‚Üí EFA
‚úî "Basic networking" ‚Üí ENI
‚úî "OS bypass" ‚Üí Only EFA
‚úî "Traffic cannot be routed / must stay within same subnet" ‚Üí EFA in OS bypass mode
‚úî "Supported on all instance types" ‚Üí Only ENI
üß† Short Mnemonics (For Exam Memory)
üí° ENI = Normal

Basic NIC ‚Üí Normal workloads.

üí° ENA = Accelerated

High performance ‚Üí "Accelerated Networking".

üí° EFA = Fastest

HPC ‚Üí "Fabric" = Super-fast communication fabric.
